   <title type="text">Tools for Studying the Hebrew Bible</title>
   <content type="html"><![CDATA[<a dir="ltr" href="https://sites.google.com/site/toolsforstudyingthehebrewbible/" id="sites-chrome-userheader-title">Tools for Studying the Hebrew Bible</a><br /><blockquote class="tr_bq"><img alt="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/9/9d/Leningrad_Codex_Carpet_page_e.jpg" height="200" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/9/9d/Leningrad_Codex_Carpet_page_e.jpg" width="173" /> </blockquote><blockquote class="tr_bq"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><span style="background-color: transparent; color: black; line-height: 1.5;">This sit</span><span style="color: black;"><span style="background-color: transparent; line-height: 1.5;">e aims to teach students how to use a set of specialized t</span><span style="background-color: transparent; line-height: 1.5;">ools for the study of the Hebrew text of the Hebrew Bible (henceforth, the Bible)</span><span style="background-color: transparent; line-height: 1.5;">. These are different from the </span></span><span style="background-color: transparent; color: black; line-height: 1.5;">tools  used for modern Hebrew because the languages are substantially  different, and because the study of ancient texts, written in "dead" or  "literary" languages, such as BH (biblical Hebrew), is fundamentally  different from the study of modern languages. &nbsp;The types of tools  presented here include</span><span style="background-color: transparent; color: black; line-height: 1.5;">:</span></span><br /><div><ol><li><span style="color: black; font-size: x-small;">Scholarly Editions of the Hebrew Bible</span></li><li><span style="color: black; font-size: x-small;">Lexica</span></li><li><span style="color: black; font-size: x-small;">Grammars</span></li><li><span style="background-color: white; color: black; font-size: x-small;">Concordances: Electronic and Paper</span></li><li><span style="background-color: white; color: black; font-size: x-small;">Other Research Tools</span></li></ol><div><span style="color: black; font-size: x-small;">I  have also included some helpful exercises designed to help students  learn how to use the major scholarly tools, as well as some other tools  that the beginning and intermediate student of biblical Hebrew may find  useful; you can navigate among these by using the toolbar on the left.</span></div></div></blockquote><blockquote class="tr_bq"><ul role="navigation"><li class=""><div dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 5px;"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><a class="sites-navigation-link" href="https://sites.google.com/site/toolsforstudyingthehebrewbible/critical-editions">Biblia Hebraica Stuttgartensia</a></span></div></li><li class=""><div dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 5px;"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><a class="sites-navigation-link" href="https://sites.google.com/site/toolsforstudyingthehebrewbible/other-critical-editions">Additional Scholarly Bible Editions</a></span></div></li><li class=""><div dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 5px;"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><a class="sites-navigation-link" href="https://sites.google.com/site/toolsforstudyingthehebrewbible/lexicons">Lexica</a></span></div></li><li class=""><div dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 5px;"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><a class="sites-navigation-link" href="https://sites.google.com/site/toolsforstudyingthehebrewbible/grammars">Grammars</a></span></div></li><li class=""><div dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 5px;"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><a class="sites-navigation-link" href="https://sites.google.com/site/toolsforstudyingthehebrewbible/concordance">Concordances</a></span></div></li><li class=""><div dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 5px;"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><a class="sites-navigation-link" href="https://sites.google.com/site/toolsforstudyingthehebrewbible/exercises">Exercises</a></span></div></li><li class=""><div dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 5px;"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><a class="sites-navigation-link" href="https://sites.google.com/site/toolsforstudyingthehebrewbible/electronic-tools">Electronic Resources</a></span></div></li><li class=""><div dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 5px;"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><a class="sites-navigation-link" href="https://sites.google.com/site/toolsforstudyingthehebrewbible/scholarly-resources">Research Tools</a></span></div></li><li class=""><div dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 5px;"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><a class="sites-navigation-link" href="https://sites.google.com/site/toolsforstudyingthehebrewbible/english-hebrew-glossary">English-Hebrew Glossary</a></span></div></li><li class=""><div dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 5px;"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><a class="sites-navigation-link" href="https://sites.google.com/site/toolsforstudyingthehebrewbible/hebrew-english-glossary-1">Hebrew-English Glossary</a></span></div></li><li class=""><div dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 5px;"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><a class="sites-navigation-link" href="https://sites.google.com/site/toolsforstudyingthehebrewbible/hebrew-english-glossary">Hebrew Chapter and Verse Numbers</a></span></div></li><li class=""><div dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 5px;"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><a class="sites-navigation-link" href="https://sites.google.com/site/toolsforstudyingthehebrewbible/the-name-of-god">The Name of God</a></span></div></li><li class=""><div dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 5px;"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><a class="sites-navigation-link" href="https://sites.google.com/site/toolsforstudyingthehebrewbible/system/app/pages/sitemap/hierarchy">Sitemap</a></span></div></li></ul></blockquote><br /><div style="text-align: center;">And see also AWOL's&nbsp; list of</div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://ancientworldonline.blogspot.com/2009/09/open-access-textbooks.html">Open Access Textbooks and Language Primers Relating to the Ancient World </a></div>]]></content>
